🛡️ 📄 Case Study on Cybercrime: Phishing Attack
Phishing is a type of cybercrime where attackers steal sensitive information such as usernames, passwords, and banking information by pretending to be a legitimate source. 
In a phishing attack, a person receives an email or a message claiming to be from a bank, social media site, or other popular sites.
The email or message may claim that they will block your account or that suspicious activities have been detected.
The email or message may include a link that takes you to a fake site that looks identical to the original site.
Once you enter your username and password or personal information on this fake site, your information is sent to the attacker.
Then, they will use your information to access your account, steal money, or misuse your personal information. 
Students and working professionals, especially those who often access various online sites, may become targets for phishing attacks.
